# :emoji: prefix(scope): Short summary
# |-- prefix: required Gitmoji keyword (e.g., feat, fix, docs)
# |-- scope: optional area affected (e.g., renderer, input)
# |-- summary: concise message (max ~50 chars, lowercase)

# Example:
# ✨ feat(ui): add dropdown menu for level selection
# 🐛 fix(physics): resolve gravity glitch on platform edge

# 🔍 Description (wrap at 72 chars, optional)
# Explain why this change was made and any relevant context.

# 💥 BREAKING CHANGE: Explain what changed and how to migrate (if needed)

# ✅ Footer (optional):
# - Closes #123


# ──────────────── Gitmoji Prefix Reference ────────────────
# :sparkles:                  feat        A new feature
# :bug:                       fix         A bug fix
# :memo:                      docs        Documentation changes
# :art:                       style       Code style (formatting, semicolons, etc)
# :recycle:                   refactor    Code change that isn't a fix or feature
# :rocket:                    perf        Performance improvements
# :white_check_mark:          test        Add or fix tests
# :fire:                      remove      Delete code or files
# :package:                   build       Package, dependency, or build system changes
# :construction_worker:       ci          Continuous integration changes
# :twisted_rightwards_arrows: merge      Merge branches
# :rotating_light:            lint        Fix or apply linting rules
# :green_heart:               fix-ci      Fix CI build
# :tada:                      init        Initial commit
# :bookmark:                  release     Tag a release
# :test_tube:                 test        Add missing tests
# :broom:                     clean       Code cleanup or dead code removal
# :detective:                 debug       Add or improve debug logs
# :coffin:                    remove      Remove dead code
